Update to match configure.in.

Support an alternate make command.

On many non-Linux platforms, the vendor-provided make command is not GNU make but either something more POSIXy or something derived from BSD, and GNU make will generally be available under a different name (usually 'gmake').  To support those platforms, allow the name of the make command to be overridden by an environment variable, with the standard 'make' as a fallback.
added compile.sh, for compiling without autoconf (./configure) and GNU Make
added |sort|uniq to mkdist.sh

Sort and deduplicate.

Some files were listed twice in this file, which lists the files to include in the distribution tarball.  This caused recent versions of GNU tar to add a spurious hard-link entry for each duplicated file, where previous versions would simply include the whole file twice.  Remove the duplicate entries, and sort the list to help prevent a regression.

Always pass -f to tar.

The code that copies the files to be distributed from the source directory into the staging directory assumes that tar, when not provided with a filename, would use stdin / stdout.  This is not the case with POSIXy tars, nor with GNU tar according to its documentation.  Use an explicit -f- instead.
